reviews.review_text:
Okay, Keith... ...now you're just showing off. ;-)

Seriously, you're making the rest of us tapers look bad!  Lovin' every minute of it, though. :-D

Excellent Scarlet>Fire This show was the first Scarlet>Fire combo I ever heard.  It's a lovely, bouncy version that doesn't get too "out there" but is still a joy to hear.    

Keith - please tell us you have an AUD for the last night of this run, 5/16.


Thanks!
AWESOMENESS This is a wonderful tape job. I was there and it was one of my favorate shows. I flew from maui to vegas only for GD shows. Mahalo and aloha
Beautiful This was the first Grateful Dead show that I ever went to. I love being able to relive this show through my speakers.
- Here we see a revival of late winter's grandeur, though the 2nd set is not as well played as the 1st.

Some interesting moments Starting at around 8:42 in the Fire, Jerry doesn't play at all for about 90 seconds. This allows for a nice rhythm section solo, with Phil and the talking drum very prominent in the  mix. This makes the Fire very interesting, rhythmically at least. 

SOTM>Sugar Mag is a nice closer, but this show doesn't have a ton of replay value.
